{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"mesodermic-preroyal-python","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Finding\n\n`src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/verify.py`'s `verify_findings()` is the shared Pass-2 kernel\nentry point that chunks findings, runs each chunk, and tallies `outcome_counts`\n(`clean`/`recovered`/`empty_outcomes`/`unrecoverable`) plus `contract_violations`. It is fully\nimplemented and unit-tested (`tests/unit/test_review_kernel.py`,\n`tests/unit/test_review_kernel_rules.py`), but neither live consumer pipeline actually calls it:\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py`'s `plan_review_decide` builds its own\n  `reshape_verifications(...)` call directly and logs+records contract violations via\n  `orchestrator.record_contract_violation(...)`, without ever calling `verify_findings`.\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py`'s `code_review_decide` (around line 401) also\n  calls `reshape_verifications(...)` directly and only `logger.error(...)`s on violations —\n  no `record_contract_violation` call, and no `outcome_counts` telemetry at all.\n\nBoth pipelines build their Pass-2 model instructions via `review_kernel.verify_instructions()`\n(the prompt-only helper) and then run the model call and reshape themselves inline, rather than\ndelegating to `verify_findings()`. So the `outcome_counts` telemetry (clean/recovered/\nempty_outcomes/unrecoverable) that ticket 1aa8-cdde-4ff6-40d0 shipped is exercised by its own\nunit tests but is not yet surfaced by either production pipeline.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/verify.py:281` — `verify_findings()` definition (chunking +\n  `outcome_counts` + `run_chunk` loop).\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py` — `plan_review_decide` calls\n  `review_kernel.reshape_verifications(...)` directly, not `verify_findings`.\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py:270` (`code_review_verify_inputs`, builds\n  instructions only) and `code_review_decide` (~line 401, calls `reshape_verifications`\n  directly, no `outcome_counts`, no `record_contract_violation`).\n- Correctness note (out of scope for this ticket): `decide.pass3_decide` already treats any\n  finding with no verification entry as `indeterminate` (`src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py`\n  around line 505-512), so the *decision* guarantee behind ticket 1aa8's AC3 already holds\n  regardless of this wiring gap — this ticket is about surfacing `outcome_counts`/contract-\n  violation telemetry uniformly, not about a verdict-correctness defect.\n\n## Remediation\n\nWire both `plan_review_decide` and `code_review_decide` to call the shared `verify_findings()`\n(or extract/reuse its chunk-running + tallying logic) so `outcome_counts` is populated and\nrecorded consistently for both consumers, and so `code_review_decide` also calls\n`record_contract_violation` (or an equivalent shared telemetry sink) on reshape violations,\nmatching `plan_review_decide`'s existing behavior. Preserve each pipeline's existing\n`impact_fn`/threshold wiring untouched.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `plan_review_decide` and `code_review_decide` both surface `outcome_counts`\n      (clean/recovered/empty_outcomes/unrecoverable) from the same shared kernel logic.\n- [ ] `code_review_decide` records contract violations via the same mechanism\n      `plan_review_decide` uses (or a documented equivalent), not only a log line.\n- [ ] Existing plan-review and code-review test suites continue to pass; new tests cover the\n      code-review pipeline's outcome_counts/contract-violation propagation specifically.\n- [ ] No change to either pipeline's decision thresholds, impact functions, or verdict shape.","id":"c2c5-53a7-2ce0-4d98","parent_id":"6eca-183e-1cd2-4fb9","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Wire shared verify_findings outcome_counts telemetry into plan_review and code_review consumer pipelines"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784691059280627001,"uuid":"8296390a-b4e0-46b5-810d-d9bf842f481d"}